  "target_response": {
    "text": "Recovery score is a composite — your device rolls overnight HRV, resting heart rate and sleep into one 0-to-100 number that estimates how ready your body is for load. It's a summary, not a measurement, which is why its confidence grade matters: today's score is rated medium confidence, so treat it as a directional gauge rather than a precise reading. Directionally, you're slightly run down: today's score of 59% is just under your 7-day average of 61%, and a bit short of your 30-day average of 63.8%. That's a nudge toward an easier day, not an alarm. If the number keeps sliding across several mornings in a row, that's when it earns a real schedule change.",
